=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_FBSineN_ex3 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright pure_tone sound, with square_like oscillator character around 700 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and compressed envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: compressed
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 700.4749
  harmonic_decay_rate: -6.1224
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9696
  pitch_clarity: 68.9827
  inharmonicity: 0.6283
  type: square_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -0.9607
  resonance_freq: 710.5957

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: FBSineN Example 3
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/FBSineN.html
// Tags: FBSineN, Classes, oscillator
// ---
// --- Example 3 ---
// increase feedback
{ FBSineN.ar(SampleRate.ir, 1, Line.kr(0.01, 4, 10), 1, 0.1) * 0.2 }.play(s);
